description: From Latin cohabitō; co- + habitō (“I dwell, I live in”).

verbs.description: cohabit (third-person singular simple present cohabits, present participle cohabiting, simple past and past participle cohabited)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To live together with someone else, especially in a romantic and sexual relationship but without being married.
(intransitive) To coexist in common environs with.
(intransitive, archaic) To engage in sexual intercourse; see coition.
